                <h3>Bonda</h3>
                <p>Bonda is a savory South Indian snack made by deep-frying a batter consisting of gram flour (besan), rice flour, and sometimes with added spices like chili, ginger, and curry leaves. The batter is typically mixed with mashed potatoes or other fillings like lentils or vegetables. Bonda has a crispy exterior and a soft, fluffy interior. It's often served with chutney or sambar.
</p>
