            <img src="imagessouth/starters/medu vada.jpeg" alt="medu">
            <div class="card-content">
                <h3>Medu Vada</h3>
                <p>Medu Vada is a popular South Indian savory fritter made from urad dal (black gram lentils) batter. The batter is seasoned with cumin seeds, curry leaves, chopped green chilies, and sometimes grated ginger. It's shaped into a doughnut-like shape with a hole in the center and deep-fried until golden brown and crispy. Medu Vada is typically served with sambar (a lentil-based vegetable stew) and coconut chutney.
</p>
                <p>Price: &#8377;120</p>
                <span style="background-color: #28a745; color: white; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px;">Veg</span>  
            </div>
        </div>
