                <h3>Mirchi Pakora</h3>
                <p>Mirchi Pakoras, also known as chili pakoras or chili bajjis, are a spicy and crispy Indian snack made from large green chilies dipped in gram flour (besan) batter and deep-fried until golden brown and crispy. The chilies are often slit open and deseeded before being dipped in the batter to reduce their heat. Mirchi pakoras are commonly served with chutney or sauce.
</p>
                <p>Price: &#8377;40</p>
